org.fujion.client

Class ClientRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fujion.client.ClientRequest
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MockClientRequest

    public class ClientRequest
extends Object
    Represents a request from the client. At a minimum, a request must have a type that dictates which handler will process the request. Most requests will also have an associated page and a data payload. The format of the data payload is specific to the request type.

      • getParam

        public <T> T getParam(String name,
                      Class<T> type)
        Returns the named parameter from the request data. This assumes that the request data is a map of parameter values. If not, null will always be returned. Performs intelligent conversion of datatypes where possible.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The expected parameter type.
        Parameters:
        name - The parameter name.
        type - The expected parameter type.
        Returns:
        The parameter value, or null if not found.

      • getParam

        Returns the named event parameter from the request.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The expected parameter type.
        Parameters:
        name - The parameter name.
        type - The expected parameter type.
        deflt - The default value for the parameter.
        Returns:
        The parameter value, or the specified default if not found.
